sentences: Leonard Gilbert Ratner (July 30, 1916 – September 2, 2011), was an American musicologist, Professor of Musicology at Stanford University,  He was a specialist in the style of the Classical period, and best known as a developer of the concept of Topic theory.
In 1947, he joined the newly formed Department of Music at Stanford University, and continued there  until his retirement in 1984 composing, teaching, and conducting research on music theory.
